      "name": "ENISA Threat Landscape 2025: Ransomware Remains Top Threat to EU Organisations",
      "description": "The European Union Agency for Cybersecurity (ENISA) has published its annual Threat Landscape report for 2025. The report identifies ransomware as the primary threat to EU organisations for the third consecutive year. Key findings include a 34% year-on-year increase in double-extortion ransomware incidents, with healthcare, finance, and government sectors most heavily targeted. The Clop, BlackCat/ALPHV, and LockBit groups collectively account for over 60% of reported incidents. The report also highlights a growing threat from state-sponsored actors in Russia, China, North Korea, and Iran conducting espionage and pre-positioning operations against critical infrastructure.",
